Head flat medially, weakly punctate, covered with rather sparse and short setae. Clypeus (
Figure 2F,G
) strongly emarginate anteriorly. Eyes (
Figure 2G
) moderately large, finely faceted, dorsally separated by about 2.0 times width of eye; interocular distance about 0.48 times head width; inner margins of eyes slightly rounded, convergent anteriorly. Maxilla with terminal palpomere (
Figure 2F
) about 2.2 times longer than wide, outer margin about 2.4 times as long as inner, subparallel along basal half, tapering apically. Labium with terminal palpomere (
Figure 2F
) at base about 0.85 times as wide as penultimate at apex. Antenna (
Figure 2H
) composed of nine antennomeres, antennomere 9 as long as antennomere 8 and tapering to apex.

Prothorax about 0.82 times basal width of elytra; pronotal base bordered; pronotal hypomeron with fovea vestigial; prosternum smooth; prosternal process (
Figure 2F
) truncate at apex, at middle about 0.24 times as wide as longer procoxal diameter; prosternum in front of coxae about 0.95 times as long as procoxal longitudinal diameter. Mesoventral intercoxal process (
Figure 2I
) about 0.95 times mesocoxal longest diameter, covered with sparse short hair; meso-metaventral junction almost straight. Metaventrite (
Figure 2I
) with complete discrimen; postcoxal lines weakly arcuate laterally, joined at middle, before junction each recurving posteriorly.

Elytral epipleuron (
Figure 2E
) with maximum width at metaventrite, narrowing posteriorly but complete to apex, with foveae vestigial.

Female genitalia (
Figure 4G,H
). Coxites triangular; sperm duct consists of two parts of almost same diameter; spermatheca (
Figure 4H
) with distinct additional gland. Infundibulum proper absent (
Figure 4G
), but bursal appendix present in the form of a sclerotized spur.
